The paper also proposes a method for feature extraction, which falls under the scope of machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of superpixel segmentation, which is a common technique in image processing and computer graphics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Fourier polar coordinates, which is a mathematical technique used in signal processing and image analysis, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for feature extraction, which involves modeling invariant behaviors, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
